'Trains travel from one town to another town all day, always on the same track, always going nonstop and at the same speed. The noon train took 80 minutes to complete the trip, but the 4 PM train took an hour and 20 minutes. Why?', 'What bird can be heard at mealtimes?', 'If there is a Yellow house on Bluebird Lane, a Green house on Orange Street, a Pink house on Kitten Road, a Black house on Whitehorse Pike and a Purple house on Firebird hill, where is the White house?', 'What building has the most stories?', 'If a chicken says, "All chickens are liars". Is the chicken telling the truth?', "When may a man's coat pocket be empty, and yet have something in it?", 'There was a man who was born before his father, killed his mother, and married his sister. Yet, there was nothing wrong with what he had done. Why?', 'The rungs of a 10 foot ladder attached to a ship are 1 foot apart. If the water is rising at the rate of one foot an hour, how long will it take until the water covers over the ladder?', 'A magician was boasting one day at how long he could hold his breath under water. His record was 6 minutes. A kid that was listening said, "thats nothing, I can stay under water for 10 minutes using no types of equipment or air pockets!" The magician told the kid if he could do that, hed give him $10,000. The kid did it and won the money. Can you figure out how?', 'When will water stop running downhill?', 'When can you add two to eleven and get one as the correct answer?', 'Romeo and Juliet are found dead on the floor in a bedroom. When they were discovered, there were pieces of glass and some water on the floor. The only furniture in the room is a shelf and a bed. The house is in a remote location, away from everything except for the nearby railroad track. What caused the death of Romeo and Juliet?', 'How many seconds are there in one year?', 'A beggars brother died, but the man who died had no brother.How could this be?', 'What can you sit on, sleep on, and brush your teeth with?', 'Name-called and favorite to eat,Has only two toes on print of feet,Colors many,Almost any Country child would have seen one.What is it?', 'Placed above it makes greater things small.Placed beside it makes small things greater.In matters that counts it always comes first.Where others increase it keeps all things the same.What is it?', 'A pet shop owner had a parrot with a sign on its cage that said "Parrot repeats everything it hears". Davey bought the parrot and for two weeks he spoke to it and it didnt say a word. He returned the parrot but the shopkeeper said he never lied about the parrot. How can this be?', 'A precious stone, as clear as diamond.Seek it out whilst the suns near the horizon.Though you can walk on water with its power,Try to keep it, and itll vanish in an hour.What is it?', 'Runs smoother than any rhyme, loves to fall but cannot climb!', 'People are hired to get rid of me.Im often hiding under your bed.In time Ill always return you see.Bite me and youre surely dead.What am I?', 'How far will a blind dog walk into a forest?', 'I know a word of letters three. Add two, and fewer there will be!', 'One winter day, there was a man standing in the middle of someones front yard. The person stayed there for several weeks without moving and the owner of the yard didnt mind. Eventually, the man left. Who was he?', 'A young boy went to a Catholic school. During school, he started goofing around, so the teacher called him out and sent him to the Pastor. Since this was a traditional school the boy would be spanked, but the Pastor believed in giving people a chance.He said, "If you can ask me a question about something you learned and I dont know the answer on the spot you will go free."The boy may have been lazy, but he was very witty. He asked, "What is it that you can see and I can see, usually every day, but God cannot see." The Pastor stood there, stumped. He couldnt figure it out because he strongly believed that God sees and knows all, and that there is only one God. The boy smiled and told him.What was it?', 'What 5 letter word typed in all capital letters can be read the same upside down?', 'What 7 letter word is spelled the same way backward and forwards?', 'A man rode out of town on Sunday, he stayed a whole night at a hotel and rode back to town the next day on Sunday. How is this possible?', 'Only one color, but not one size, Stuck at the bottom, yet easily flies. Present in sun, but not in rain, Doing no harm, and feeling no pain. What is it?', "You have me today, Tomorrow you'll have more;As your time passes, I'm not easy to store;I don't take up space, But I'm only in one place;I am what you saw, But not what you see. What am I?",


'Black within, red without, with four corners, roundabout. What is it?', 'As I went across the bridge, I met a man with a load of wood which was neither straight nor crooked. What kind of wood was it?', 'Formed long ago, yet made today, Employed while others sleep. What none would freely give away. Nor any wish to keep. What is it?', 'Man walks over, man walks under, in times of war he burns asunder. What is it?', 'In a tunnel of darkness lies a beast of iron. It can only attack when pulled back. What is it?', "What is something you don't own but you can give it to anyone you meet? You only have one, but you can give it away as many times as you want without losing it. What is it?", "Big as a biscuit, deep as a cup, even a river can't fill it up. What is it?", "A dozen Royals gathered round, Entertained by two who clowned. Each King there had servants ten, Though none of them were also men. The lowest servant sometimes might, Defeat the King in a fair fight. A weapon stout, a priceless jewel, The beat of life, a farmer's tool. What is it?", "The Pope has it but he does not use it. Your father has it but your mother uses it. Nuns do not need it. Your lady friend's husband has it and she uses it. What is it?", 'Nothing on the outsideNothing on the insideLight as a featherYet ten men cannot lift it.What is it?', 'What can climb mountains, cross streams, handle hundreds of feet each day, yet never moves? What is it?', 'My name is two letters. You call many people by this name, but yet their first name is not this. What is it?', "White bird, featherless, flyin' out o' paradise, flyin' over sea and land, dyin' in my hand. What is it?", 'My teeth are sharp, my back is straight, to cut things up it is my fate. What am I?', 'Where is the AD before BC, tomorrow before yesterday, and the eight is first?', 'Which word in the English language becomes shorter when it is lengthened?', 'Rock and roll, rock and roll. What rocks but does not roll?', 'What is often returned but never borrowed?', 'Used to threaten, used to defeat. Sometimes it grows, sometimes it shrinks. Used to conquer, used to protect. It marks your downfall, it marks your success. The true god of war, the creator of mess. What is it?', 'Often held but never touched, always wet but never rusts, often bites but seldom bit, to use me well you must have wit. What am I?', 'What has no hands but might knock on your door, and if it does you better open up?', 'What never gets any wetter, no matter how much it rains?', "It goes up, but at the same time goes down. Up toward the sky, and down toward the ground. It's present tense and past tense too, come for a ride, just me and you. What is it?", 'Marble walls as white as milk, lined with skin as soft as silk, in a fountain crystal clear, a golden apple will appear, there is no key to this stronghold, yet theives break in and steal the gold. What is it?', 'What has 88 teeth but never brushes them?', 'The leaves are on the fruit, The fruits is on the leaves. What is it?', 'Glittering points that downward thrust, sparkling spears that never rust. What is it?', 'Never resting, never still. Moving silently from hill to hill. It does not walk, run or trot, All is cool where it is not. What is it?', 'What can go up and come down without moving?', 'You can see it every day, But cannot ever touch it. What is it?',


'I am a container without hinges, a lock, or a key, yet a golden treasure lies inside me. What am I?', 'Hot or cold, running or still, hard or soft, I can be anything. What am I?', 'What vegetable always fails in every competition, yet is a fantastic rapper?', 'I am clean, but not water.I am white, but not snow.I am sweet, but not ice cream.What am I?', 'I am called the most romantic fruit on the planet. What am I?', 'Two mothers and two daughters went out to eat. Each one of them had one burger, yet only three burgers were eaten. How is this possible?', 'What is the tastiest kind of money?', 'What did the doctor prescribe to the sick lemon?', 'What vegetable is the king of rock and roll?', 'What fruit is always sad?', 'I am a beer yet kids can drink me and never get drunk. What am I?', 'I am a food that explodes. But long before I explode, I am already dead. I can be small, I can be big, and I can be fragrant. What am I?', 'Do you know a fruit that is friendly and enjoys meeting new people?', 'What vegetable is the most fun to be around and the one that everybody wants to hang out with?', 'A woman shoots her husband. Then she holds him underwater for over 5 minutes. Finally, she hangs him. A few minutes later they both go out together and enjoy a wonderful afternoon together. How can this be?', 'Can you name three consecutive days without using the words Monday, Tuesday, Wednesday, Thursday, Friday, Saturday, or Sunday?', 'The more you take, the more you leave behind. What am I?', "I have thousands of ears, but I'm a really bad listener. What am I?", 'Some months have 30 days, and some months have 31 days. How many have 28?', 'Two trains enter a one-way tunnel at different ends exactly at 9:00, But they both come out the other end unharmed 5 minutes later.  How is this possible?', 'A plane with 50 passengers crashes into a mountain and everyone is killed, but there were only 49 bodies. How is this possible?', 'I come once in a minute, twice in a moment, but never in a thousand years. What am I?', 'I am always in you and sometimes on you. If I surround you, I can kill you. What am I?', 'What are moving left to right, right now?', 'I belong in the month of December, but not in any other month. I am not a holiday either. What am I?', 'No matter how little or how much you use me every day, you change me every month. What am I?', 'Why were the inventors of the airplane believed they could fly?', 'I protect, I stand tall. The reason for my existence is to strike fear in all. What am I?', 'If one train in New York is going 1206 mph and one in Florida goes 305 mph which one will get to Cuba first?', 'Those who make me are likely to break me, what am I?',


